    • Description

      • A line cook is a culinary professional who is responsible for preparing and cooking food items in accordance with the chef's specifications, ensuring timely delivery and high-quality presentation of dishes. They operate within a specific station in the kitchen, such as grilling, sautéing, or preparing sauces, and are tasked with setting up their station with necessary supplies, prepping ingredients like chopping vegetables or butchering meat, and cooking menu items in collaboration with the rest of the kitchen staff. Line cooks must maintain cleanliness and adhere to food safety standards, manage inventory, and work efficiently under pressure to contribute to the overall customer satisfaction and smooth operation of the restaurant

    • Skills

      • Contract-based

    • Description

      • A janitor, also known as a custodian or cleaner, is responsible for maintaining the cleanliness, hygiene, and overall appearance of facilities such as schools, offices, hospitals, and public buildings. Their duties typically include sweeping, mopping, and polishing floors, cleaning and sanitizing bathrooms, restocking supplies, and disposing of trash. Janitors may also perform minor repairs, handle light maintenance tasks, ensure the proper functioning of facilities, and secure buildings by checking for unlocked doors or operational issues. They play a crucial role in creating a safe and welcoming environment by adhering to health and safety regulations and may be required to operate cleaning machinery and handle cleaning chemicals with care.
